Use 'snapshot' suffix for version In Maven, you only use non-snapshot named versions for your tagged release,
'-snapshot' indicates that this is just the latest snapshot in a series of
code development. Without the '-snapshot' suffix, the artifact is assumed
to be immutable, and unique for that version.

The '1.3.0-SNAPSHOT' versions are what comes before you releasing the final
'1.3.0' release. I'm nudging the version back here so as not to confuse
the maven release plugin.

Add pom fields to meet Maven Central Sync Requirements https://docs.sonatype.org/display/Repository/Sonatype+OSS+Maven+Repository+Usage+Guide#SonatypeOSSMavenRepositoryUsageGuide-6.CentralSyncRequirement

Also use the Sonatype OSS Parent POM to make releasing easier.
